\section{Results}
\label{sec:Results}

The following sections describe the model results from each of the scenarios. Output variables include changes to groundwater, crop yield and farmer income. 

\noindent \textbf{Groundwater}\\
To evaluate model operation, modelled groundwater outputs (1971 to 2013) are compared to the best available observed groundwater data (Figure \ref{fig:gw1}). Observed data lies within the range of modelled outputs in all four study districts, and largely mirrors the trends of reported groundwater levels. The median modelled outputs are used as a baseline for comparison across all other modelled scenarios. Modelled changes in groundwater levels due to predicted climate change are shown in Figure \ref{fig:gwblrcp}. In the northern districts of Sitapur and Sultanpur, groundwater levels are predicted to remain largely unchanged. In the southern district of Jalaun, modelled groundwater levels increase by approximately 5 meters over baseline conditions by 2005. Water levels in Hamirpur under RCP 8.5 are expected to fall approximately 5 meters while remaining to baseline conditions under RCP 4.5. 


